    {
      "number": 4,
      "id": "I_kwDOIRf-ms5XokGB",
      "title": "Poly1305 is referred to as a HMAC, which it isn't",
      "url": "https://github.com/BlockchainCommons/WIPs-IETF-draft-envelope/issues/4",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "simonratner",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Several places in https://blockchaincommons.github.io/WIPs-IETF-draft-envelope/draft-mcnally-envelope.html refer to HMAC:\r\nSections 1.5, 2.2.3, and 3.3.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n> When used with envelopes, the `crypto-msg` construct `aad` (additional authenticated data) field contains the digest of the plaintext, authenticating the declared digest using the Poly1305 HMAC.\r\n\r\nI believe Poly1305 isn't technically an HMAC (which refers to a specific MD-hash-based construction).\r\nReplacing with `MAC` without narrowing it further is probably fine.",
      "createdAt": "2022-11-30T21:42:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-12-02T01:10:26Z",
      "closedAt": "2022-12-02T01:10:26Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 6,
      "id": "I_kwDOIRf-ms5c0Qx1",
      "title": "Progressive Trust",
      "url": "https://github.com/BlockchainCommons/WIPs-IETF-draft-envelope/issues/6",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "shannona",
      "authorAssociation": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "If it seems appropriate for the IETF format:\r\n* I would suggest the phrase \"progressive trust\" in the privacy-ready section of the intro link to https://www.blockchaincommons.com/musings/musings-progressive-trust/. \r\n* We can also optionally add a brief definition. Here's what we have in the IETF Lexicon: **Progressive Trust.** The concept of gradually building trust over time.\r\n\r\nIt feels somewhat important because this is more our term of art than something in super-common usage.",
      "createdAt": "2023-01-25T20:04:31Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-01-26T01:24:45Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "ChristopherA",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "I\u2019d love to have a slightly longer short definition, which includes the concept that there is no absolute trust, and that progress toward reasonable trust to mitigate risks for all parties is the goal. ",
          "createdAt": "2023-01-25T20:20:23Z",
          "updatedAt": "2023-01-25T20:20:23Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "shannona",
          "authorAssociation": "CONTRIBUTOR",
          "body": "Here's a longer alternative:\r\n\r\n**Progressive Trust.** The concept of gradually building trust over time. This model of trust presumes that there is no absolute trust: no trust registry or trust framework. Instead, trust is developed more as in real life, where gradually expanding trust mitigates risk among parties.",
          "createdAt": "2023-01-26T01:24:45Z",
          "updatedAt": "2023-01-26T01:24:45Z"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
